        "summary": "AI should be agentic, adaptable, and aligned with people.\n\nI’m Gohar Hany — a CS graduate (2025) focused on Agentic AI, automation, and GenAI-driven solutions. I design and deploy intelligent systems that automate decision-making, enhance user experience, and scale across workflows.\n\nMy toolkit includes Gemini API, LangChain, FAISS, Supabase, and n8n — tools I’ve used to build AI agents, learning assistants, inventory bots, and customer support solutions serving 500+ users.\n\nMy background in public relations and education allows me to bridge the gap between technical systems and human needs. I’ve led 80+ partnerships, delivered nationwide campaigns, and trained individuals in communication, tech, and leadership.\n\nI’m particularly passionate about Agentic AI — creating modular agents that reason, remember, and act with autonomy. I’m excited about roles and collaborations where I can apply automation and GenAI to build systems that matter.",
