                "description": "During my summer internship at the Information Technology Institute (ITI), I gained comprehensive experience in supervised machine learning. The training covered:\n\nFeature Data Types: Exploring how to classify and analyze different types of data for effective use in models.\nData Quality: Understanding how to assess and improve data quality to ensure model accuracy and minimize errors.\nStrategies for Handling Missing Values: Applying techniques to address missing values and maintain the integrity of analysis.\nTransforming Categorical Data: Learning how to convert categorical data into formats suitable for model analysis.\nHandling Outliers: Identifying and managing outliers to enhance model performance.\nScaling: Implementing data scaling techniques to improve model performance and accuracy.\nI also worked with a variety of machine learning models, including:\n\nLinear Regression\nLogistic Regression\nSupport Vector Machines (SVM)\nPolynomial SVM\nK-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)\nDecision Trees\nAdditionally, I developed a solid understanding of key concepts such as:\n\nGradient Descent\nConfusion Matrix\nAccuracy, Recall, Precision, F-score\nData Pipeline\nCorrect Data Splitting Techniques to Avoid Data Leakage\nThis internship provided me with a robust foundation in supervised machine learning and practical skills that I am excited to apply to future projects.",
